=== SD1.1 ===
SD1 is refined by in-zooming Treating Patient in SD1.1.
Patient is an object, physical.
Patient can be incoming, triaged, under treatment, stabilized, discharged, or deceased.
Emergency Physician is an object, physical.
Treatment Protocol is an object, informatical.
Medication Inventory is an object, physical.
Blood Bank is an object, physical.
Operating Room is an object, physical, environmental.
Vital Status of Patient is an object, informatical.
Vital Status of Patient can be normal, abnormal, or critical.
Defibrillator is an object, physical.
Ventilator is an object, physical.
Assessing Severity is a process, informatical.
Administering Medication is a process, physical.
Performing Surgery is a process, physical.
Monitoring Vital Status is a process, informatical.
Stabilizing Patient is a process, physical.
Treating Patient is a process, physical.
Treating Patient zooms into Assessing Severity, parallel Administering Medication and Performing Surgery, Monitoring Vital Status, and Stabilizing Patient, as well as Vital Status of Patient, in that sequence.
Emergency Physician handles Assessing Severity.
Emergency Physician handles Performing Surgery.
Assessing Severity requires Treatment Protocol.
Assessing Severity affects Treatment Protocol.
Administering Medication consumes Medication Inventory.
Performing Surgery consumes Blood Bank.
Performing Surgery requires Operating Room.
Monitoring Vital Status requires Vital Status of Patient.
Stabilizing Patient changes Patient from under treatment to stabilized.
Stabilizing Patient changes Vital Status of Patient from abnormal to normal.
Administering Medication requires Defibrillator.
Performing Surgery requires Ventilator.

=== SD2 ===
SD is refined by in-zooming Diagnosing Condition in SD2.
Patient is an object, physical.
Medical Record of Patient is an object, informatical.
Medical Record of Patient can be incomplete, complete, or archived.
Emergency Physician is an object, physical.
Laboratory is an object, physical, environmental.
Imaging Suite is an object, physical, environmental.
Lab Sample is an object, physical.
Lab Report is an object, informatical.
Lab Report can be pending or finalized.
State pending of Lab Report is initial and default.
State finalized of Lab Report is final.
Imaging Report is an object, informatical.
Imaging Report can be pending or finalized.
State pending of Imaging Report is initial and default.
State finalized of Imaging Report is final.
Collecting Sample is a process, physical.
Ordering Lab Work is a process, informatical.
Processing Lab Report is a process, informatical.
Performing Imaging is a process, physical.
Interpreting Finding is a process, informatical.
Updating Medical Record is a process, informatical.
Diagnosing Condition is a process, informatical.
Diagnosing Condition zooms into Collecting Sample, parallel Ordering Lab Work and Performing Imaging, Interpreting Finding, and Updating Medical Record, as well as Lab Sample and Lab Report and Imaging Report, in that sequence.
Emergency Physician handles Interpreting Finding.
Collecting Sample yields Lab Sample.
Ordering Lab Work requires Lab Sample.
Ordering Lab Work requires Laboratory.
Ordering Lab Work affects Lab Report.
Processing Lab Report handles exception from Ordering Lab Work.
Processing Lab Report changes Lab Report from pending to finalized.
Performing Imaging requires Imaging Suite.
Performing Imaging changes Imaging Report from pending to finalized.
Interpreting Finding requires Lab Report.
Interpreting Finding requires Imaging Report.
Interpreting Finding affects Medical Record of Patient.
Updating Medical Record changes Medical Record of Patient from incomplete to complete.

=== SD3 ===
SD is refined by unfolding Trauma Alert Level in SD3.
Trauma Alert Level is an object, informatical.
Trauma Alert Level can be green, yellow, red, or black.
State green of Trauma Alert Level is initial and default.
Activating Alert is a process, informatical.
Escalating Alert is a process, informatical.
Declaring Mass Casualty is a process, informatical.
Deactivating Alert is a process, informatical.
Trauma Alert Level unfolds in SD3 into Activating Alert, Escalating Alert, Declaring Mass Casualty, and Deactivating Alert.
Activating Alert changes Trauma Alert Level from green to yellow.
Escalating Alert changes Trauma Alert Level from yellow to red.
Declaring Mass Casualty changes Trauma Alert Level from red to black.
Deactivating Alert changes Trauma Alert Level to green.
